### Linting & Code Formatting
- Enforce code formatting with Prettier and Stylelint
- Require zero lint errors (ESLint, Stylelint) before merge
- Use pre-commit hooks (`lint-staged`, `husky`) for auto-lint/format
- Add CI check for linting, type-checking, and formatting

### CI/CD & Branching Strategy
- All pull requests must pass CI (type-check, lint, build, test)
- Use GitHub Actions, CircleCI, or similar platforms for pipelines
- Adopt trunk-based or Git Flow branching based on team preference
- Require descriptive PR titles, summaries, and linked issues

### Environment Variables & Secrets
- Separate safe/public and secret/server-only env variables
- Never commit secrets or API keys to version control
- Use `.env*` files with proper `.gitignore` settings
- Regularly rotate sensitive tokens and credentials

### Performance Budgets & Monitoring
- Define and enforce bundle size and load-time budgets
- Track Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS) via monitoring tools
- Run Lighthouse CI in pipeline for regression checks
- Monitor with Sentry Performance or Web Vitals libraries

### Dependency Management
- Evaluate and approve new dependencies for bundle size and security
- Schedule regular upgrades and removal of deprecated packages
- Forbid inclusion of vulnerable or unmaintained dependencies
- Run `npm audit`/`yarn audit` as part of CI

### Collaboration & Workflow
- Limit PR size to facilitate effective reviews
- Include screenshots for UI changes in PR descriptions
- Reference issues/tickets directly in PR summary
- Use team workflows for assigning, tracking, and closing issues

### Documentation & Developer Experience
- Use Storybook for live documentation of UI components
- Update architecture diagrams for major system changes
- Keep a detailed "Setup & Getting Started" section up to date
- Add code comments for complex logic and critical flows
- Maintain centralized documentation for common patterns and gotchas

### Security
- Implement input sanitization to prevent XSS attacks.
- Use DOMPurify for sanitizing HTML content.
- Use proper authentication methods.



